SYNOPSIS
Based on the epic graphic novel by Frank Miller, 300 is a ferocious 
retelling of the ancient Battle of Thermopylae in which King Leonidas 
(Gerard Butler) and 300 Spartans fought to the death against Xerxes and 
his massive Persian army. Facing insurmountable odds, their valor and 
sacrifice inspire all of Greece to unite against their Persian enemy, 
drawing a line in the sand for democracy. The film brings Miller&#039;s 
(Sin City) acclaimed graphic novel to life by combining live action with 
virtual backgrounds that capture his distinct vision 
of this ancient historic tale.
